## 5. Why The Purple User Bubble Shows Workspace Context

In the screenshots, the user bubble includes text like:

```text
---
Current workspace context from the editor:
workspace_root: /home/...
active_file: /src/App.tsx
active_editor_content:
...
open_files:
...
Use this already-open workspace...
```

This comes from the frontend legacy compatibility path in:

```text
apps/frontend/src/lib/agent-client.ts
```

Relevant function:

```text
legacyRunAgentRequest(req)
```

What it does:

- takes the user's prompt
- appends workspace context text
- sends it as one old-style `{ prompt }` request when the newer rich request
  shape is rejected by an older sidecar

Why it appears in the UI:

- the prompt text can become visible as part of the user message history
- it makes Ask mode look noisy, even though the context is useful for the model

Ideal UX rule:

```text
Workspace context should help the model.
Workspace context should not visually pollute the user's chat bubble.
```

Recommended future improvement:

- keep workspace context in the typed request payload
- show only the original user text in the chat bubble
- if needed, show context as a small collapsed "Context used" row

