## 6. Visual Feedback Message Types

### User message bubble

Owned by:

```text
apps/frontend/src/lib/store.ts
apps/frontend/src/features/agent/AgentTimeline.tsx
```

Created when:

- `sendUserMessage` appends a local `Message`
- `AgentTimeline` renders it as `MessageBubble role="user"`

Purpose:

- show what the user asked

Should contain:

- user text
- optional attached file mention

Should not contain:

- huge injected system context
- raw tool JSON
- internal backend details

### Assistant message bubble

Owned by:

```text
apps/frontend/src/lib/store.ts
apps/frontend/src/features/agent/AgentTimeline.tsx
```

Created when:

- stream emits `token` or `message.delta`
- `ensureAssistant` creates the assistant item
- `appendDelta` updates text live

Purpose:

- show the answer
- stream text as the model responds

### Workspace analysis card

Owned by:

```text
apps/frontend/src/lib/store.ts
apps/frontend/src/features/agent/AgentTimeline.tsx
services/agent/src/llama_studio_agent/agent/orchestrator.py
```

Created from events:

```text
agent.context.loading
agent.context.ready
run.context_ready
```

Agent mode:

- visible

Ask mode:

- suppressed by `consumeStream`
- hidden by `buildAskTranscript`

### Plan card

Owned by:

```text
services/agent/src/llama_studio_agent/agent/planner.py
services/agent/src/llama_studio_agent/agent/orchestrator.py
apps/frontend/src/lib/store.ts
apps/frontend/src/features/agent/AgentTimeline.tsx
```

Created from events:

```text
plan.created
plan
plan_step
```

Agent mode:

- visible when planner runs

Ask mode:

- backend sets `skip_planner = true`
- frontend also suppresses plan events defensively

### To-do card

Owned by:

```text
services/agent/src/llama_studio_agent/agent/orchestrator.py
apps/frontend/src/lib/store.ts
apps/frontend/src/features/agent/AgentTimeline.tsx
```

Created by:

```text
todo_write virtual tool
TodoUpdateEvent
```

Agent mode:

- visible

Ask mode:

- backend sets `enable_todos = false`
- `todo_write` is not exposed
- if a model calls it anyway, backend no-ops it
- frontend suppresses todo events defensively

### Tool activity card

Owned by:

```text
services/agent/src/llama_studio_agent/tools/*
services/agent/src/llama_studio_agent/agent/orchestrator.py
apps/frontend/src/lib/store.ts
apps/frontend/src/features/agent/AgentTimeline.tsx
```

Created from events:

```text
tool_call
tool.started
tool.completed
```

Visual statuses:

```text
pending
running
ok
failed
cancelled
approval
```

Screenshot example:

```text
Tool activity
write_file
status: failed
error: not approved: missing permission: write_fs
```

Meaning:

- model tried to write a file
- permission engine denied it
- UI correctly showed failure instead of pretending success

### Diff/review card

Owned by:

```text
services/agent/src/llama_studio_agent/agent/workspace_diff.py
services/agent/src/llama_studio_agent/v1/agent_run.py
apps/frontend/src/features/agent/DiffCard.tsx
apps/frontend/src/features/diff/DiffReviewView.tsx
```

Created when:

- Agent mode produces file changes
- review-before-apply flow prepares a diff

Ask mode:

- never should show diffs

