## 8. Step-By-Step: User Sends A Message

```text
1. User types in Composer.
2. Composer validates non-empty message.
3. Composer calls sendUserMessage(content).
4. store.ts expands @file if present.
5. store.ts creates a local user message item.
6. store.ts creates deterministic runId: run-local-...
7. store.ts builds RunAgentRequest.
8. agent-client.ts opens SSE stream and POSTs /agent/run.
9. v1/agent_run.py validates session and workspace.
10. v1/agent_run.py chooses Ask or Agent config.
11. orchestrator.py emits lifecycle events.
12. orchestrator.py streams model output and tool events.
13. agent-client.ts yields AgentEvent objects.
14. store.ts consumeStream applies or suppresses events by mode.
15. AgentTimeline renders Ask transcript or Agent workflow cards.
```

