## 13. Acceptance Checklist For This Flow

Ask mode is correct when:

- user bubble shows only the user's message
- assistant bubble gives the answer
- no workspace analysis card appears
- no plan card appears
- no to-do card appears
- no tool activity card appears by default
- no write/shell action is allowed
- header says `Zoc Ask`
- subtitle says `Read-only answers`
- composer shows `Read-only`

Agent mode is correct when:

- header says `Zoc Agent`
- subtitle says `Auto run`
- tool activity cards show tool input/output/error
- failed tool permissions show red error feedback
- successful tools show green pass/ok feedback
- plans and to-dos are visible when the agent is doing real work
- diffs require review/apply flow before touching real workspace

Backend is correct when:

- Ask mode uses `ASK_SYSTEM_PROMPT`
- Ask mode sets `skip_planner = true`
- Ask mode sets `enable_todos = false`
- Ask mode restricts tools to read/search/status tools
- Agent mode can use normal planner, todos, tools, review flow, and permission
  checks

